The White House has been urging Congress to pass $22.5 billion in COVID-19 spending, warning that the U.S. is running out of money to fight the virus. And the Republicans are a hurdle as they are insisting that funds must be spent somewhere else, other than on the pandemic. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Song Yaotian argues that the bigger problem than the rebound in the pandemic, is that the U.S. government has no money to fight it.